  "prompt": "Are Territorial army officers getting permanent commission now a days?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Territorial Army officers in India generally serve in a part-time capacity and are not typically granted permanent commissions. The Territorial Army is primarily designed for citizens who serve on a voluntary, part-time basis, and the roles primarily supplement the regular Indian Army during times of need. Consequently, officers in the Territorial Army are generally not considered for permanent commission, which is a pathway more commonly associated with full-time regular army officers.\n\nFor the latest developments or changes in policy regarding this matter, I recommend consulting official Indian Army resources or recent government announcements, as policies can evolve over time.",
